    "In this regard, it is believed that one key aspect determining entity categorization is the length feature of entities.",
    "The author employed rotational location embedding to collect the relational information between the head and tail characters.",
    "The outcomes of comprehensive studies performed on five benchmark datasets such as the GENIA, ACE2005, ACE2004, Resume and MSRA which showed that relative location information can increase the accuracy of entity recognition pairings.",
    "At last, the model achieved F1-values of 86.66%, 85.83%, and 81.33%, which are, respectively, 0.06%, 0.43%, and 1.32% better compared with the innovative baseline model.",
